description.narrative:
The main objective of the the event to commemorate the 15 Years anniversary of the Protocol to the African Charter on Human and People’s Rights on the Rights of Women in Africa (the Maputo Protocol) was to engage Member States, CSOs and other stakeholders to garner momentum towards the continental wide ratification, implementation and domestication of the Maputo Protocol. The specific objectives include; 
(i) to develop an action plan, including identifying the role of civil society actors and policy interventions to accelerate ratification and advance implementation of the Maputo Protocol; and
(ii) to reaffirm the AU, United Nations and CSOs commitment to work towards the promotion of women’s rights and gender equality on the continent.
